    <h1>Chrome Extensions</h1>
    <p>Chrome extensions are small software programs that customize and enhance your browsing experience on the Google Chrome browser. There are thousands of extensions available on the Chrome Web Store, ranging from productivity tools to entertainment add-ons.</p>
    <h2>Installing Chrome Extensions</h2>
    <p>To install a Chrome extension, simply navigate to the Chrome Web Store and search for the extension you want. Click on the "Add to Chrome" button and follow the prompts to install the extension. Once installed, the extension will appear in your browser's toolbar.</p>
    <h2>Popular Chrome Extensions</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/grammarly-for-chrome/kbfnbcaeplbcioakkpcpgfkobkghlhen">Grammarly</a> - A grammar and spell-check tool.</li>
      <li><a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/adblock-plus-free-ad-blo/mcfkgaicjnkjbnmibmmejfmhfoihkdgn">Adblock Plus</a> - A popular ad blocker.</li>
      <li><a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/pocket/mjcnijlhddpbdemagnpefmlkjdagkogk">Pocket</a> - A tool to save and read articles later.</li>
      <li><a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/honey/bmnlcjabgnpnenekpadlanbbkooimhnj">Honey</a> - A shopping tool that finds and applies coupon codes.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Creating Chrome Extensions</h2>
    <p>If you want to create your own Chrome extension, you can use web technologies such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The Chrome Developer website provides documentation and tools for building extensions.</p>
